{
  "name": "Knowledge Overwhelming",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 14th level, you can unleash a magical wave of pure knowledge to overwhelm the minds of lesser beings. As an action, you can cause up to five creatures within 30 feet of you to make an Intelligence saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes psychic damage equal to 4d8 + your Intelligence modifier, and it is stunned until the end of its next turn. On a successful save, it takes half damage and is not stunned. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
